nonzeroCoef = function (beta, bystep = FALSE) 
{
### bystep = FALSE means which variables were ever nonzero
### bystep = TRUE means which variables are nonzero for each step
  nr=nrow(beta)
  if (nr == 1) {#degenerate case
    if (bystep) 
      apply(beta, 2, function(x) if (abs(x) > 0) 
            1
      else NULL)
    else {
      if (any(abs(beta) > 0)) 
        1
      else NULL
    }
  }
  else {
    beta=abs(beta)>0 # this is sparse
    which=seq(nr)
    ones=rep(1,ncol(beta))
    nz=as.vector((beta%*%ones)>0)
    which=which[nz]
    if (bystep) {
      if(length(which)>0){
        beta=as.matrix(beta[which,,drop=FALSE])
        nzel = function(x, which) if (any(x)) 
          which[x]
        else NULL
        which=apply(beta, 2, nzel, which)
        if(!is.list(which))which=data.frame(which)# apply can return a matrix!!
        which
      }
      else{
        dn=dimnames(beta)[[2]]
        which=vector("list",length(dn))
        names(which)=dn
        which
      }
        
    }
    else which
  }
}

Preparing boxplotting at the end

Set up, ready for running models for 50 times and 75:25 for data split

n = length(Y)
ntest = round(n * 0.25)
ntrain = n - ntest
all.test.id = matrix(0, ntest, 50)

for (i in 1:50){

  Ytest.pred = predict(full.model, newdata = myData1[test.id,])
  MSE1[i,1] = mean((myData$Y[test.id] - Ytest.pred)^2)
  
  #ridge lse
  cv.out = glmnet(X[-test.id, ], Y[-test.id], alpha = 0,lambda = lam.seq)
  Ytest.pred = predict(cv.out, s = cv.out$lambda.1se, newx = X[test.id,])
  MSE1[i,2] = mean((Y[test.id] - Ytest.pred)^2)
  
  # ridge min
  Ytest.pred = predict(cv.out, s = cv.out$lambda.min, newx = X[test.id,])
  MSE1[i,3] = mean((Y[test.id] - Ytest.pred)^2)
  
  #lasso min
  cv.out = glmnet(X[-test.id, ], Y[-test.id], alpha = 1,lambda = lam.seq)
  Ytest.pred = predict(cv.out, s = cv.out$lambda.min, newx = X[test.id,])
  MSE1[i,4] = mean((Y[test.id] - Ytest.pred)^2)
  
  
  # lasso lse
  Ytest.pred = predict(cv.out, s = cv.out$lambda.1se, newx = X[test.id,])
  MSE1[i,5] = mean((Y[test.id] - Ytest.pred)^2)
  
  #refit
  tmp.X = X[, colnames(X) %in% var.sel]
  mylasso.refit = coef(lm(Y[-test.id] ~ tmp.X[-test.id,]))
  Ytest.pred.refit = mylasso.refit[1] + tmp.X[test.id,] %*% mylasso.refit[-1]
  MSE1[i,6] = mean((Ytest.pred.refit - Y[test.id])^2)


  #pcr
  pcr_pred <- predict(pcr_model, X[test.id,])
  MSE1[i,7] = mean((pcr_pred - Y[test.id])^2)

  
}
